You can then sort the array using the `sort()` method and rejoin it back into a string using the `join()` method. Here's a sample script: 

``` 
function myFunction() {
  var text = "17,15,44,22,8"; // input string
  var array = text.split(","); // split string into array
  array.sort(function(a, b) { // sort array
    return a - b; });
  var result = array.join(","); // rejoin array back into string
  return result; // return result
}
``` 

3. If none of those options work for you, you can also sort the list manually, which is obviously not recommended.
